Chihara Junior

24
00:00:26,470 --> 00:00:29,540
Kimura Yuichi

25
00:00:26,870 --> 00:00:31,540
[everyone] Good evening

26
00:00:30,580 --> 00:00:32,680
So that's how it looks like, huh

27
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:33,550
Good evening

28
00:00:33,550 --> 00:00:35,910
How come you knew about this place?

29
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:37,850
You know, 'cause it's famous

30
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:40,350
Oh, is that so? Thank you. A place for two?

31
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:40,820
Yes

32
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:43,350
Master, did someone ever sat in here?

33
00:00:43,350 --> 00:00:45,120
This thing is really...

34
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:46,390
It does... get in your way

35
00:00:46,390 --> 00:00:47,460
Can I move it away?

36
00:00:47,460 --> 00:00:50,290
Of course you can, do as you please

37
00:00:50,290 --> 00:00:53,160
Someone must have placed this here (before)

38
00:00:51,460 --> 00:00:53,160
He's already acting rude

39
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:55,600
It's stuck on his mind

40
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:58,400
Only 10 years ago he would have gone berserk about it

41
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,870
Just because of that?!

42
00:00:59,870 --> 00:01:01,870
Now he has calmed down

43
00:01:01,870 --> 00:01:03,810
I just asked if I could move it

44
00:01:03,810 --> 00:01:07,680
One time he got mad just by looking at a rental k-car

45
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:08,180
For real?

46
00:01:08,180 --> 00:01:12,220
"Why would I go to a car-rental if they have k-cars?!"

47
00:01:12,220 --> 00:01:14,890
And his face was bright red

48
00:01:14,890 --> 00:01:15,790
That's for couples

49
00:01:15,790 --> 00:01:18,160
One time he got really made at some guy who was

50
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,590
Buying a Pocari Sweat at 22:00

51
00:01:19,590 --> 00:01:20,490
Why is that?

52
00:01:20,490 --> 00:01:24,290
He was like "the fuck are you buyin' that at this hour?!"

53
00:01:23,030 --> 00:01:24,530
What the hell, why?!

54
00:01:24,290 --> 00:01:25,860
It was saturday

55
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:29,270
It felt like that "saturday's just starting" thing

56
00:01:29,270 --> 00:01:32,470
Well, you had your reasons

57
00:01:32,470 --> 00:01:34,000
Yeah, it's a matter of timing

58
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,370
It must be a long time since you two know each other

59
00:01:37,370 --> 00:01:39,210
Right?     - Yeah, it's been a long time

60
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:42,710
Me too, it's been almost 30 years

61
00:01:42,710 --> 00:01:46,020
Since I got to know and work with Downtown

62
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:49,520
And I surely received lots of kind words from them

63
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,520
Is that so?

64
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,690
Yeah, really...

65
00:01:51,690 --> 00:01:52,790
From who?

66
00:01:52,790 --> 00:01:56,160
Well, since today's your birthday...

67
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:59,460
Oh, thank you so much, really

68
00:01:56,690 --> 00:02:05,200
September 8th - Matsumoto Hitoshi is 55 y.o.

69
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:02,530
It's kinda embarrassing but I'm now 55

70
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:05,200
55 years, man...

71
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,840
So in this timespan...

72
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:10,340
Today Matsumoto's young colleagues, whom he knows for a long time,

73
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:10,340
will talk about all the kind words he ever said to them to this day

74
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:10,340
He said lots of kind stuff to you, right?

75
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:10,340
Yeah, he told me so many nice things

76
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:14,010
You remember the first Gaki DVD?

77
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:18,110
How many years has passed since? Like 10 years...?

78
00:02:18,110 --> 00:02:19,680
You mean our first one?

79
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,450
Yeah the very first one

80
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:22,980
Which featured the batsu game

81
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:26,790
From that batsu game, lots of DVDs were made

82
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:27,390
15 of them, I think

83
00:02:27,390 --> 00:02:29,990
And around the eight volume...

84
00:02:29,990 --> 00:02:32,230
The "Yamazaki vs Moriman"

85
00:02:32,230 --> 00:02:34,230
DVD too    - Yeah, yeah

86
00:02:34,230 --> 00:02:35,330
Was released

87
00:02:35,330 --> 00:02:38,330
Once per year, around June

88
00:02:38,330 --> 00:02:41,700
I got paid for its sales income

89
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:46,640
And that sum was the same for more than once

90
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:49,780
Even around when we were
doing the "Moriman Showdown"

91
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:52,280
I got paid the same amount

92
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:55,980
And I thought "ohh, that's nice",
then I got a call from Matsumoto

93
00:02:55,980 --> 00:02:57,550
And he told me by phone

94
00:02:57,550 --> 00:03:01,560
"Yamazaki, how's the income
for the Moriman Showdown?"

95
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:05,190
I was like "Huh? The DVD? Same as always"

96
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:07,460
And he "What? The same as always?"

97
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:10,400
"You mean for the Moriman Showdown?" - "Yes, that"

98
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,430
"And it's the same? - "Yes it is"

99
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:14,570
He said "Oh, I see",

100
00:03:14,570 --> 00:03:15,970
And our call ended

101
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,370
Then, one day

102
00:03:18,370 --> 00:03:22,340
I was doing some stuff
and looked at my bankbook

103
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:26,150
And I noticed that the same sum I was
been payed through all those years

104
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:28,650
Has been payed once more the next day

105
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,880
I mean, for the DVD, by Yoshimoto

106
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:35,720
I thought "What?" and on our next
Gaki session I asked Matsumoto

107
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:39,630
"You know, I got the same amount payed again"

108
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:42,430
And when I was about to say
"Could it be a mistake?"

109
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,500
He said "That... you know"

110
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:47,130
"This is not money meant for us"

111
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:50,140
"So you have to take it instead"
- that's what he said

112
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,500
And so...

113
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:55,710
What's that story about?     - Huh?

114
00:03:56,540 --> 00:03:57,710
What do you mean?

115
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:59,110
I have no idea...

116
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:00,180
What do you mean?

117
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,280
What do I mean?!

118
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:05,380
I mean, what I'm saying is that

119
00:04:05,380 --> 00:04:10,090
About the Moriman Showdown DVD, Matsumoto...

120
00:04:10,090 --> 00:04:11,790
You got payed more than usual?

121
00:04:11,790 --> 00:04:12,890
Was it doubled?

122
00:04:12,890 --> 00:04:13,620
It was

123
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:15,990
You didn't say that

124
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:17,400
That's the unclear part

125
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,660
I said it

126
00:04:18,660 --> 00:04:21,130
I said the same sum got payed twice

127
00:04:21,130 --> 00:04:24,170
Oh? twice... just say it before!

128
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:25,370
It was doubled

129
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:27,370
Now we got it 'cause you said it

130
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:28,040
Yes, right

131
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:30,070
It's always like that

132
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:33,880
He always makes mistakes

133
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:33,880
when saying good stuff about me

134
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,880
It was an important part too

135
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,080
That was the core

136
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,020
It's always like this, today too

137
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:39,820
Now I get it

138
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:42,790
What are you doin' on Ochiken?

139
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:45,690
note: short nickname for "rakugo kenkyuu kai" - rakugo research club. (ochi = raku)

140
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,790
Don't call it "Ochiken"!!

141
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:43,850
He did it again

142
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:45,060
I hate that nickname!

143
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:47,790
He always fucks up each good talk about me he's doing

144
00:04:47,790 --> 00:04:50,260
Did I make mistakes? I was careless

145
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:51,760
Now it makes sense

146
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:52,460
Sorry

147
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:54,960
So, it was doubled?     - Yeah, same sum twice

148
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,970
I got the same sum payed twice

149
00:04:56,970 --> 00:05:00,600
And that's because Matsumoto-san
made it possible, right?

150
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,640
But say it, man...      - I got what you mean

151
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:04,940
You got it, right?     - Sorta

152
00:05:04,940 --> 00:05:08,940
I mean, he was not the type of person to get it himself

153
00:05:08,940 --> 00:05:12,210
He didn't try to understand it      - That's right

154
00:05:12,210 --> 00:05:13,020
Did it really happen?

155
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:14,380
It's real     - I see

156
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:16,390
And that's because Matsumoto told you so

157
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:18,050
Yeah, he told me that

158
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:20,060
Yes, I did say that

159
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:20,820
See?

160
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:23,660
I said that wasn't money me and Hamada deserved

161
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:26,560
It was the fruit of Yamazaki's hard work alone

162
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,560
And so we didn't need that payment anymore

163
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,400
No matter how many DVDs we sold

164
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,230
I told that to manager Okamoto

165
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:34,500
And he said "got it", and so did our agency

166
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:37,540
But I thought "will he notice it?"

167
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:40,310
And so I got them to deposit the sum on his account

168
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:43,380
To confirm that I asked him that     - I see

169
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,110
On the phone, about the income

170
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:46,780
And he was like "nothing changed"

171
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,320
And thought "that's not good"      - I see

172
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,390
If that would have happened

173
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:54,590
I'd be like "Well, I'll get Hamada fired from this company"

174
00:05:55,190 --> 00:05:56,290
Hamada?

175
00:05:56,290 --> 00:05:58,760
Why me?

176
00:05:57,630 --> 00:06:00,900
You'd place all the blame on him

177
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:01,230
Why it has to be me?

178
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:05,530
That's cause his sense of justice is half-assed

179
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:07,000
When that happened

180
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,540
I thought "man, he's such"

181
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,500
"An honest person"

182
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,740
And I'm not saying it as an excuse

183
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:15,610
An honest person?

184
00:06:15,610 --> 00:06:17,140
I thought you'd say more

185
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,510
What's that?

186
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,880
An honest person?

187
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:23,520
His praising skills always suck when it comes to me

188
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,950
I mean----

189
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:28,890
Wouldn't you think he was honest on that?

190
00:06:28,890 --> 00:06:30,120
Yeah but, "honest"?

191
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:32,330
I'd say "he's so kind" or something

192
00:06:32,330 --> 00:06:33,990
Yeah, that would have been good

193
00:06:33,990 --> 00:06:35,360
You had to

194
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,030
I mean like, "sincere"

195
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,130
Say "sincere" then!

196
00:06:38,130 --> 00:06:39,970
He was "sincere"     - Yeah, not "honest"

197
00:06:39,970 --> 00:06:42,340
Oh come on! It's the same thing!

198
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:45,140
Is that the mood this episode's going to have?

199
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:46,940
It's not our fault he was the first

200
00:06:46,940 --> 00:06:50,510
I mean, the staff already handed me this handkerchief

201
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:51,910
It's good you're all set up

202
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:55,510
There's no right timing to use it right now

203
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:57,950
I just want to wipe off this weird sweat

204
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:59,350
Well, at least you're sweating

