I don't like this    - Don't go

213
00:07:14,130 --> 00:07:16,770
If we're talking about knowing each other...     - Yes?

214
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,970
Me too since I've joined Gaki no Tsukai...

215
00:07:19,970 --> 00:07:22,470
It's been 22 years to this day

216
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:24,210
You all took care of me

217
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:27,580
And there were countless times

218
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:32,020
In which I've received kind words from him

219
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:34,250
I don't really remember---

220
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:36,790
I mean, I don't recall

221
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,490
Saying all these kind words

222
00:07:38,490 --> 00:07:41,230
I think you     - You just don't remember saying them

223
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:43,260
Exactly      - But those who heard them do

224
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:46,860
For me there was something you said I can't forget

225
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:51,300
We always have this Gaki No Tsukai
new year's party episode every year

226
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:53,770
And one time, after it

227
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:57,310
There were Matsumoto, Housei
and Fujiwara from License

228
00:07:57,310 --> 00:08:00,140
Together with me and the writer Takasu

229
00:07:57,310 --> 00:08:01,810
note: he's talking about Takasu Mitsuyoshi

230
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:03,150
And we all decided to go have a drink

231
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,650
For how many years have we...?

232
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:08,120
I think it's like 6 years we're doing this

233
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:11,860
And so, we were all talking while drinking alcohol

234
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:14,920
It was about 2 years ago

235
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,260
And as we were normally drinking

236
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:20,800
Everyone started to talk a bit
about their job-related worries

237
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:24,900
And we all wanted to talk
to Matsumoto about them

238
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:30,340
And so we discussed freely
about them, that was the mood

239
00:08:30,770 --> 00:08:33,610
And at that time

240
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:36,710
I was trying to came in contact with ZIP

241
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:37,950
note: a japanese morning news/entertainment show

242
00:08:36,710 --> 00:08:39,650
And looking for movies to play in

243
00:08:39,650 --> 00:08:45,620
I was kinda trying to find something else besides
comedy, like my animals picture book promotion

244
00:08:45,620 --> 00:08:50,830
I just happen to be in a situation in which
I wanted to have more comedy-unrelated jobs

245
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:54,630
But I was thinking "am I cut for this?"

246
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:56,430
I mean, I thought that too about Gaki

247
00:08:56,430 --> 00:08:59,470
I'm always wondering
if I'm actually cut for this

248
00:08:59,470 --> 00:09:02,970
And so, in this period in which
I was shrouded in such worries

249
00:09:02,970 --> 00:09:06,610
Thinking about stuff like
"can I do this job properly?" and such

250
00:09:06,610 --> 00:09:09,880
I asked Matsumoto for some advice

251
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:12,680
And he told me
"Don't think too much about it, Tanaka"

252
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:14,750
"Because, Tanaka, I think that..."

253
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:19,820
"The best thing about you is that you always
do the jobs you have to do with utmost effort"

254
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:24,830
"And you're always doing jobs fit for yourself"

255
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:28,360
"You're always aware of things,
just like the size of your body"

256
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:32,570
"You can choose by yourself the clothes
you wear, and you do the same with jobs"

257
00:09:32,570 --> 00:09:34,770
"So don't sweat it about genres or such"

258
00:09:34,770 --> 00:09:38,370
"Wouldn't it be good just to do the jobs you think are best for you?"

259
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:40,470
That's what he said to me

260
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:45,410
And it lead me to choose the job I'm doing now

261
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:45,410
note: Tanaka is currently the host of ZIP

262
00:09:46,010 --> 00:09:47,080
Yes...

263
00:09:48,210 --> 00:09:50,080
I don't remember that...

264
