00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:19,650
Well, Endo's case is different

273
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:23,020
But Tanaka was going through a lot

274
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:26,590
So I told him to do what he likes to

275
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:28,790
D-did you remem---

276
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:32,620
It's not that I clearly remember it
or I forgot about it...

277
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:36,290
It's just weak

278
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,930
Well, that's how it is inside you

279
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:43,330
It's surely way stronger inside Tanaka

280
00:10:43,570 --> 00:10:46,240
Man, he just told you about his feelings!

281
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:48,740
Yeah, I was like "aww, man!"

282
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:50,540
I mean, there's been a lot of stuff

283
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:52,140
I think that's a good thing

284
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:54,480
He lead you, right?
- Yes, it was thanks to him

285
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,710
It's not like I despise it---

286
00:10:56,710 --> 00:10:59,080
It's like some teaching from Buddha, right?

287
00:10:59,080 --> 00:10:59,850
Right

288
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:03,490
It's a way to show how thankful you are

289
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:07,560
That's what I thought, it gave me strenght

290
00:11:08,690 --> 00:11:11,300
I think it was like... 20 years ago

291
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,260
I've been doing lots of stuff in Osaka

292
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:17,230
And when they ended, I came to Tokyo

293
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:20,240
But there was hardly any work in Tokyo for me

294
00:11:21,170 --> 00:11:27,010
The kind words Matsumoto said to Junior on their first show together

295
00:11:27,510 --> 00:11:30,210
I think it was like... 20 years ago

296
00:11:30,210 --> 00:11:32,220
I've been doing lots of stuff in Osaka

297
00:11:30,610 --> 00:11:39,360
Junior when he was younger

298
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:36,120
And when they ended, I came to Tokyo

299
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:39,720
But there was hardly any work in Tokyo for me

300
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:42,560
And I was like "what do I do now?"

301
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,530
At that time

302
00:11:44,530 --> 00:11:47,600
There was this show, "warai no jikan" (time for laugh)

303
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,600
Which Matsumoto was doing on Asahi TV

304
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,830
With Imada, right?     - Yes

305
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:52,470
So, at the time

306
00:11:52,470 --> 00:11:54,270
On their first episode

307
00:11:54,270 --> 00:11:57,970
They had gathered like 20 Yoshimoto comedians

308
00:11:57,970 --> 00:12:02,440
And the plan was just to have them talk freely

309
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:06,680
That was the first time I ever worked with Matsumoto

310
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:12,790
So, when I was in Oosaka I always
relied on Itao who took care of me

311
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:19,260
So when it was my turn to talk,
I talked about an episode I had with him

312
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:21,430
While I still was very nervous

313
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:25,130
There was this one time we went to the Koushien

314
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:25,130
note: a baseball tournament

315
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:28,240
And they fired some jet balloons
from the 7th inning's bottom

316
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:30,040
So, they fired it from there

317
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:34,740
And the same goes from the other innings

318
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:39,010
Then I have no idea how, but when
they fired it from the ninth inning

319
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:41,720
Even though there were like 55 thousand people

320
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:45,220
That ballon, with a one in a 55 thousands chance

321
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:47,720
Landed straight on his head

322
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:52,960
And while I was like "Woah!" he didn't move an inch

323
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,730
He still had the balloon on his head

324
00:12:56,060 --> 00:13:00,270
At one time the plastic tip fell and hit his forehead

325
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:02,170
And without even moving

326
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:03,870
He just swiped it off

327
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:06,670
When I said this story to them

328
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:08,440
The audience laughed at it

329
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:15,620
So, we all had a closing party after it and
we all went there to have a drink or such

330
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:20,320
And around when it was about to end,
Matsumoto went to me and told me

331
00:13:22,290 --> 00:13:28,690
"I think that your story about Itao was the funniest today"

332
00:13:28,690 --> 00:13:30,760
And then he got back home

333
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:33,900
Those words really had a huge impact on me

334
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:36,800
And thinking about them I thought that maybe

335
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,670
I could have a chance in Tokyo

336
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:39,140
I see

337
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:41,870
Looking back at it I think that those words

338
00:13:41,870 --> 00:13:44,380
Are still echoing inside my head

339
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:47,450
Do you remember that?

340
00:13:47,950 --> 00:13:49,280
I don't...

341
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:52,420
Either way, they're here

342
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:53,050
That's right

343
00:13:53,050 --> 00:13:54,420
They're still here

344
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:55,890
They had an impact     - Yeah

345
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:59,220
See? It's good they're talking about it

346
00:13:59,220 --> 00:14:02,430
You may not remember,
but they still have them here

347
00:14:02,430 --> 00:14:04,860
It's just... they're faint

348
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:07,730
It was a good story, yes?

349
00:14:07,730 --> 00:14:09,200
Yeah, it was

350
00:14:09,770 --> 00:14:10,700
Shouzo, do you...?

351
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:12,670
Yes, I...

352
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:16,070
You know, I've remarried 3 years ago     - Yes

353
00:14:16,070 --> 00:14:18,880
And I had to make lots of arrangements for it

354
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:22,250
And between them, the most important to me

355
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:25,420
Was about the daughter I had from Chiaki, my ex-wife

356
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:28,820
Which was a mid-schooler by
the time I was getting remarried

357
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:31,420
So it was a pretty emotional time for me

358
00:14:31,420 --> 00:14:33,820
I've been thinking about how to told my daughter

359
00:14:33,820 --> 00:14:37,230
I mean, should I told her beforehand or after it?

360
00:14:37,230 --> 00:14:41,730
I didn't want her to be involved and felt
like talking to her about it wasn't good

361
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:46,300
And while I was thinking that much about
the right timing to tell my daughter about it

362
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:48,410
Some journalist out there

363
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:52,240
Was pretty quick to slam my remarrying news on paper

364
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:55,080
My current wife is now pregnant

365
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:57,480
And I know that from my daughter point of view

366
00:14:57,480 --> 00:15:02,850
It's something like "daddy married another woman
plus there's a chance I'll have a brother or a sister"

367
00:15:02,850 --> 00:15:08,120
And I know that if I was her age, I'd panic over this

368
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:10,930
And so when I saw that news on the Sanspo newspaper

369
00:15:10,930 --> 00:15:15,230
I thought "Woah, this is the worst..."

370
00:15:15,230 --> 00:15:18,630
So I talked about it with Matsumoto,

371
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:23,740
And I was like "what should I do about it?"
and felt flustered about it

372
00:15:23,740 --> 00:15:26,310
And at that time Matsumoto was like

373
00:15:26,310 --> 00:15:31,410
"There, there...", he tried to cheer me up

374
00:15:31,410 --> 00:15:35,680
And I just keep saying "man, I'm so
pissed off about it, what should I do?"

375
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:40,990
The next day on the show Matsumoto
was taking part in, "Wide na Show"

376
00:15:40,990 --> 00:15:46,760
I was really feeling down and trying
my best to let my rage fade away

377
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:49,730
I also have the DVD from back then

378
00:15:49,730 --> 00:15:50,900
Can I put this on?

379
00:15:52,530 --> 00:15:53,940
He got that too?     - Yes

380
00:15:56,600 --> 00:16:00,670
You know, Endo from Cocorico
is going to get married again

381
00:16:00,670 --> 00:16:05,750
And he has already a kid and he's been
thinking about the right timing to say it

382
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:08,250
I'm talking about the daughter
he had with Chiaki

383
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:12,090
And she knows there could be a chance
she could get a brother or sister in law

384
00:16:12,090 --> 00:16:15,760
Endo is thinking a lot about this, that's
why he's feeling down about it

385
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:18,530
Because even though he wanted to tell
her by his own timing

386
00:16:18,530 --> 00:16:22,830
But the Sanspo newspaper wrote it first

387
00:16:22,830 --> 00:16:28,540
And his daughter was shocked by it
I mean, something like that...

388
00:16:28,540 --> 00:16:31,170
It's not something you want for your kid

389
00:16:31,170 --> 00:16:35,910
I'd like to know from these jerks what's
the point of writing that stuff

390
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:38,610
'Cause it really pissed me off

391
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:42,780
When I watched this

392
00:16:42,780 --> 00:16:46,390
I felt really relieved, it's as if

393
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:51,920
Matsumoto put on words everything
I had in mind right in front of the public

394
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:54,630
And I thought "man, he really saved me"

395
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:58,430
And when the year ended, on the New Year's party

396
00:16:58,430 --> 00:17:01,300
I thought I had to say thanks to him directly

397
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:07,170
So I went and I said "Thank you so much for
saying that, you really helped me to calm down"

398
00:17:07,170 --> 00:17:09,310
And then Matsumoto at that point

399
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:15,650
Inside this whole "let's not talk about it" atmosphere,
looked at my face for few seconds and said

400
00:17:15,650 --> 00:17:17,650
"Sure."

401
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:30,260
That's what you kindly told me

402
00:17:30,830 --> 00:17:32,430
"Kindly" told you?     - Yes

403
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:35,500
Yes well, you already...

404
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:41,010
Said everything on that show, so your
"Sure, it's okay" was enough for me

405
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:44,910
Really, that's it

406
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,110
Well, just so you know...

407
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:51,520
Kimura has been crying for a while by now       - What?!

408
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,420
That's impressive

409
00:17:54,820 --> 00:17:56,420
I mean, his sensitivity

410
00:17:57,650 --> 00:17:59,020
Come on, man!

411
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:04,830
It's going on for a while by now     - For real?

412
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:08,830
I mean, he's really impressive, he's crying for a while now

413
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:13,740
I think he's worth receiving Kiyohiko Ozaki prize record

414
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:13,740
note: a japanese singer

415
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:15,570
Who decided that?!

416
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:17,510
Sorry for that

417
00:18:19,010 --> 00:18:21,740
I really

418
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:23,210
Do feel you guys

