432
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:05,420
My job was to raise and lower the curtains,

433
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:08,020
Downtown were doing their signature abduction skit

434
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:13,230
I remembered there was hardly any
applause at first, and when I was leaving

435
00:19:13,230 --> 00:19:17,670
There was this thunder of applause inside
the teather because how funny it was

436
00:19:17,670 --> 00:19:21,640
Like this, every day was filled with emotion for me

437
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:26,540
One time they decided to have this quiz-skit

438
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:29,680
It lasted for about ten days

439
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,680
What I felt about it

440
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:33,350
On the opening day

441
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:39,050
There was a problem with the intro, it should have
been about one asking what's the height of Mt. Fuji

442
00:19:39,050 --> 00:19:41,820
And the other had to come up
with an answer and scold him

443
00:19:41,820 --> 00:19:45,660
And then they did other stuff, but

444
00:19:45,660 --> 00:19:53,670
But they kept on doing it for then days, always answering
a new question with answers from previous days

445
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:56,400
And as I kept on watching it

446
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:59,910
And I was having goosebumps

447
00:19:59,910 --> 00:20:03,640
I happen to notice the mekuri
with "Downtown" written on it

448
00:19:59,910 --> 00:20:07,910
note: a paper signboard displaying comedians name / manzai duo names on stage

449
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:07,280
So I took it off and went to the guy who wrote it

450
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:12,690
And told him "go make a new one, you can't
have them be on stage with such filthy mekuri"

451
00:20:12,690 --> 00:20:15,050
So I had him make a new one

452
00:20:16,060 --> 00:20:19,220
That was the first time I ever thought

453
00:20:19,220 --> 00:20:22,900
I had to do my best myself too

454
00:20:24,030 --> 00:20:26,200
The atmosphere...

455
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:29,430
And clothes too... everything was really cool there

456
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,940
So...

