00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:50,590
As you know in the 90s Gottsu Ee Kanji ended

463
00:20:50,590 --> 00:20:55,530
But we also had a special episode
around the beginning of 2000

464
00:20:55,530 --> 00:21:01,170
So, after we finished airing it,
we all decided to go to the pub

465
00:21:01,170 --> 00:21:03,630
You know, to wrap things up

466
00:21:03,630 --> 00:21:05,600
I was there too, a bit late

467
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:09,610
There were also Matsumoto
Imada, Takasu and YOU

468
00:21:09,610 --> 00:21:11,880
Even Higashino... he came later

469
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,040
Also Junior was there

470
00:21:14,340 --> 00:21:17,350
So I saw them and said "good morning"

471
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:20,350
"It's 9"

472
00:21:22,850 --> 00:21:24,720
"What? Are you 29 y.o.?"

473
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,860
"Nope, it's just 21:00"

474
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:29,660
And I was like "whaaaat!"

475
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:33,000
"What the heck"

476
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:38,070
So, as we kept chatting and drinking

477
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:41,640
Matsumoto went and to each one of us...

478
00:21:42,940 --> 00:21:44,710
I think he was a bit drunk

479
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:48,780
While pointing his finger at us,
he started saying really nice stuff

480
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:54,480
"YOU, you're this this and this,
and so this", like that

481
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:56,790
"And Higashino, you're this"

482
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:58,250
"Imada, you..." etc.

483
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:01,160
And it was my turn

484
00:22:02,420 --> 00:22:03,960
He said "Kimu..."

485
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:09,360
"You know, this guy lives on a

486
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:09,360
170'000 yen monthly rent house"

487
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:09,360
note: roughly 150$ / 130€

488
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:11,570
"But if we have to base it on his merit..."

489
00:22:11,570 --> 00:22:16,610
"There's no way he'll have to live in such a cheap place"

490
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:19,570
"Kimura, I'm sure that one day..."

491
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:25,650
"You'll live in a 1'000'000 yen monthly rented mansion"

492
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:25,650
note: roughly 8900$ / 7700€

493
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:27,820
...That's what he said to me

494
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:32,650
I'm so thankful

495
00:22:37,220 --> 00:22:40,730
Also, back then your mobile
phone was a two-touch dial...

496
00:22:45,470 --> 00:22:51,840
Kimura will talk about another memory with Matsumoto

497
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:54,940
So, Matsumoto,you had a two-touch dial phone

498
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:55,940
Two-touch dial?

499
00:22:55,940 --> 00:22:58,950
Those old ones in which
by pressing the number buttons

500
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:01,050
You'd call an assigned number

501
00:23:01,050 --> 00:23:03,050
It was some time ago

